<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbdc99a02-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s6914a"><num value="6914a">§ 6914a.</num><heading> Labeling of lubricating oil</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of any provision of law which requires the labeling of commodities, lubricating oil shall be treated as lawfully labeled only if it bears the following statement, prominently displayed:</chapeau><level style="-uslm-lc:I81" id="idbdc99a03-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading>“DON’T POLLUTE—CONSERVE RESOURCES; RETURN USED OIL TO COLLECTION CENTERS”.</heading><content />
</level>
<sourceCredit id="idbdc99a04-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/89/272/tII/s2005">Pub. L. 89–272, title II, § 2005</ref>, as added <ref href="/us/pl/96/463/s4/a">Pub. L. 96–463, § 4(a)</ref>, <date date="1980-10-15">Oct. 15, 1980</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/94/2056">94 Stat. 2056</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbdc99a05-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbdc99a06-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="idbdc99a07-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">A prior <ref href="/us/pl/89/272/s2005">section 2005 of Pub. L. 89–272</ref> was renumbered section 2006 and is classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s6915">section 6915 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
</section>
